  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice <strong>half </strong>your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining onion </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663666304988-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663666304988-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663666304988-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663666304988-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1663666304988-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>lamb mince</strong> to a medium bowl with the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>onion</strong>,<strong> half </strong>your <strong>beef stock mix </strong>(you'll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and mix thoroughly until fully combined (clean hands is the best way!) – this is your <strong>lamb mixture</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> lamb mixture</strong> to one side of a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) and shape into a loaf[ves]</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20-25 min or until browned – this is your <strong>lamb meatloaf</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663666310986-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663666310986-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663666310986-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663666310986-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1663666310986-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the meatloaf is cooking, chop your<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add<strong> </strong>the<strong> chopped potatoes </strong>and<strong> peeled garlic </strong>to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender then drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663666318257-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663666318257-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663666318257-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663666318257-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1663666318257-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a very low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-9 min or until softened and caramelised</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Return the <strong>drained potatoes & garlic</strong> to a low heat with a splash of <strong>milk</strong>,<strong> </strong>a knob of <strong>butter </strong>and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and mash until smooth – this is your <strong>garlic mash</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1663666326302-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1663666326302-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1663666326302-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1663666326302-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1663666326302-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>lamb meatloaf</strong> with the <strong>garlic mash</strong>, spread it<strong> </strong>with the back of a spoon to cover the top of the meatloaf, then fluff with a fork</p><p>Return the meatloaf to the oven for a final 15 min or until the potato is golden and crispy and the lamb is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>garlic mash topped lamb meatloaf</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1663666334288-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1663666334288-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1663666334288-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1663666334288-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1663666334288-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the<strong> remaining beef stock mix </strong>in 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[350ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>onion marmalade </strong>– this is your <strong>onion beef stock</strong></p><p>Once the onion has caramelised, increase to the heat to medium and add 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 1 min or until the flour has dissolved</p><p>Once dissolved, whisk in the <strong>onion beef stock</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 7-8 min or until thickened to a gravy-like consistency – this is your <strong>onion gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1663666338922-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1663666338922-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1663666338922-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1663666338922-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1663666338922-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>blanched peas </strong>with a small splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to a large heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the peas are hot</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
